Martins Ifijeh The Reddington Zaine Laboratory (ZaineLab) promoted by the Reddington Hospital Group has been accredited by the Lagos State Government for PCR COVID-19 Testing. This was conveyed in a letter dated August 11, 2020 to the management of the Reddington Group by the Executive Secretary Lagos State Health Facility and Monitoring and Accreditation Agency (HEFAMAA), Dr Abiola Idowu. Reddington ZaineLab located at 6b Bendel Close, off Bishop Aboyade Street, Victoria Island is equipped with state-of-the-art Class 3 Biosecurity Safety Technology which delivers results within 24-48 Hours. According to the Reddington ZaineLab and Armoured Shield Medical Director
Dr Olusola Oluwole, we are the only private hospital in Lagos currently accredited both for Testing and Treatment of COVID19 and Sample Collection Centres are being arranged in Victoria Island, Ikeja GRA and Lekki for the convenience of everyone especially those requiring testing for travel purposes.